TextBlock.TextLine: London Edmund warner
Antwerpen 29 gb 1681
th
S. my lust to you was on the 22: curitt with invoyce for the packett N.6 which I hope
with you by this time, for was att menporte the 23: I hope also that N4 & 5 prove
to content & that non of either shall be opened before you receive them
for I am sure no boddy elce doth pack them more closely, because I have the
sending forward of many others & know their doing, so that I should mch
wonder, that yd freind. complaines, as if my packetts are to thich, which
& understand by yd of 11 curitt whoever to comply with yd order have
made up the packett N.7„ in paper parcells as you rnoted & is gou forward
yeasterray of which in closee is the invoyce, for which finding right pleyd
to give mee creditt all the crawatts are booader, as also them in N.8 &
so that & hope they be well, for non broader are demanded that I kmow
I have sent N. 92„ & 102 though I had no order for such low prijses yett
haveing sent severall of such sort that proved well & these beeng verl
good cheap didventer to putt them by the more, because I alwages
anderstood, that low prijses render best, I am aproviding the rest
as also them of the luped ground with duble pures or lupes, and shall
asort them as well as possible & send forward as soon as I can I could
thim to please to recommend itt spetially to yd freindat dover
as for any goods to have from England if swas accquainted with
what yd dealing, is shall be willing to give you an acctt of what
might turne to proffitt, for you may be sure of my endeavours to pleap
@ 29 ditto 7
my freinds, whilst I remaine
London John Loyd
th
S. in answer to yd of 11: curitt I am vere much troubled, that I can not send
ytt yett this post the promised cortificatie because the notary is avere
leasy fellow, to go to the witnesses, yett he promised I should have itt
this day, if itt comes, shall include itt inthis: & wonder the
prijses of tykes do not in corridge, seeng they are att the oldrate
of which when you please you may command I shall send to bruges
2 or 3 bales to be ready to be shipt if any frost should hinder the
passage from hence thether, there fore you may resolve once more
for I shall not be able to provide any more before next spring the
clover seed is att bruges by this time, & have bought itt in the pays de
waes were is their staple, & forind of severall prijses, old seed att
2 ft: 2½ & 3 as also some meeatt the same prijses, ss not knowing if itt
be for a perticular uso, or atryall have brought ther vere best that
was to be had & the fellow would not devide the parcell, so was
forceed to take itt all seeng 167 att 3 ¼
for the barrele & buying & tolles & schipping
for fraight & char gesto gent
butt as itt have not the charges att gant or bruges which when I know shall
advise you butt if you wanted great quantities, I could well assort mun
& told seeds, so that they should not coste above 2 ½ a 3 t pr e2
be good to yd jonuwno: I shall endeavour also to procure yd pietteres as
well as beany iust now receave a bavrell IMN.1 fromt in John balle
for yd actt. itt beeng with yarne, soplease to advise mee the low
twijses & may selt them att for ready mony & then you shall see
what I shall be able to do in barter, pes you shall be plansed
to order mee if you have itt cheap, & do promise my self to in
corridge you for a large trade & to with seinde salutot
pray overrate not the year
butt first pennce & assure yd self
of my endeavours toyd most advemtedge
Antw: 29 gb 1681 1do
London Henry Maynard
S. on the 26: curitt was to you my last with a remise for £140:- on peeterrmidy, sence
rec. yd of 14 ditto as for the 6.N silver marck in case you supose, or be sure to proviide
some more about next spring, I am contented you lett them alone till chave
seen you for I shall want non before marck next though the last be sold: inclosed
me
ƒ50:- due 21 of next month on Jolin dinneswill for which please to procure
the needfull & pass to my acctt mr. baudies hath not yett limitedanctto
somme, though I have payd already about £300: which seeng you will
have to be past to yd acctt. shall be don accordingly thoughto dis charge
my grant actt you might vero w transferre 2 £300: onne
att such rate as you iudge convent, not to disturs yd aggree made
about that, whoever, so as y please, for what I pay oneway or other
shall dininish ether - intrim you know yd coming over where you
must lodge, therefore & give no greater unvitation, butt assure you
that you will be heardtely willecom & I doubt, not butt you will finde
all things ready, so desire my acctt onely att yd depart ure for I hope
to make some remise more I have sold all our worster strifes, & have
been agreat foll not to have in ordered in angusts 1oop patience
pray if anything may be recommanded to expedition lett this be vet
the sending forward of 10 or 12 hale frises more as for merly butt
bevould not have them altogheter so brouwne, butt distnetely of
mixture & cullours, so pray send them froward with all imaginable
speed & wrap them with one manchester bay provide, alsoon other balots
cont. 8 asp scrankins bayes with the greenstreepkens and gred lifts de oushire
bayes to be vrappered with - a white cotton anoth bale to cont. 12 dems
cottonso £24 & 25 pence a goad of the verebest that you can providee
& send them as soore you roudge convement butt above all minde the
worste frises for Enmst hand them here within & wee ke derw

monsr. Dese weeke verwaght bij ul 3 packen waer van MN. 52 tegens
dondagh savonts hier moet sijn soo sal ul daer voor sorgen tselve p wagen
te senden & dandere 2 scheepe van hier nae costij vertrekt p. beurtschip
men
een pack & N18 mert tijken om tselve nae brugge te senden aende A
coots voor mijn ordre waer mede blijve
Brugge Raphael Coots
mons. 29 past. was aen ul mijnen lesten sedert de ul van 28 & 29 becomen
teversenden van de goederen onlondon is wel, betarck ul voor sijne prompe
gratus festellen over de lakens, doch wegens de rechte nier alsoo die in faref
vrij sgaen ul rek van disbourse sal exaimeeren & ul volgens creditt
ben blijde dat John simons is gearriveert de 3 packen sien gegemoet
gelijk pr mijne leste hebbe versoeght te neminste het pack N 52, f welke
wenschte donderdagh aenstaende hier was, want ick daerom ben verlegen
& dander liver adroiture tegemoett sien soo sal ul mij verobligeeren
tselve te depescheeren, sende nae costij een packtijken om tot mijnder ordre
te be waeren daer en tusschen ul dienaer hadde geirne deprovenu verkoghte
lakens waer van noch seenis onbetaelt den simon hoevenaerts evenwel gelieft
hem £46:1„ 8 te vergoeden op conditie soo dat van ditto hoevenaerts niet onfangen
